1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about the spacing effect than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:10,800
The spacing effect suggests that spreading out learning over time leads to better retention.

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,000
Yet, many believe cramming works just as well.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,600
But does it really?

5
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:20,000
Research shows spaced learning can enhance memory recall by over 50%.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,600
So, next time you study, try breaking it up!

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,600
Your brain will thank you.

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,600
Curious for more science tips?

